{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17651517","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17651517"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:25:22+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:25:22+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18470"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18470","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18470"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.01,0.85,0.07,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11199"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79473"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11199","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11199"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18470"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64795"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4900"},{"type":"tags","id":"4903"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4927"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"6648"},{"type":"tags","id":"6652"},{"type":"tags","id":"6812"},{"type":"tags","id":"9906"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"26014"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26021"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79473","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79473"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe pulmonary circulation is a vital component of the cardiovascular system, carrying blood between the heart and lungs for gas exchange.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the correct sequence of blood flow through the pulmonary circulation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Left ventricle \u2192 pulmonary arteries \u2192 lungs \u2192 pulmonary veins \u2192 right atrium","Right atrium \u2192 pulmonary veins \u2192 lungs \u2192 pulmonary arteries \u2192 left ventricle","Right ventricle \u2192 pulmonary arteries \u2192 lungs \u2192 pulmonary veins \u2192 left atrium","Right ventricle \u2192 pulmonary veins \u2192 lungs \u2192 pulmonary arteries \u2192 left atrium","Left atrium \u2192 pulmonary arteries \u2192 lungs \u2192 pulmonary veins \u2192 right ventricle"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct sequence is \u003Cstrong\u003Eright ventricle \u2192 pulmonary arteries \u2192 lungs \u2192 pulmonary veins \u2192 left atrium\u003C/strong\u003E. Deoxygenated blood is pumped from the right ventricle into the pulmonary trunk, which divides into right and left pulmonary arteries. These arteries branch progressively into smaller arterioles and then into capillaries surrounding the alveoli where gas exchange occurs. Oxygenated blood then flows through pulmonary venules, which merge to form the pulmonary veins that return blood to the left atrium.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect sequences are:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELeft ventricle \u2192 pulmonary arteries \u2192 lungs \u2192 pulmonary veins \u2192 right atrium\u003C/strong\u003E - The left ventricle pumps blood into the systemic circulation, not the pulmonary circulation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERight atrium \u2192 pulmonary veins \u2192 lungs \u2192 pulmonary arteries \u2192 left ventricle\u003C/strong\u003E - Blood flows from the right atrium to the right ventricle before entering pulmonary arteries\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELeft atrium \u2192 pulmonary arteries \u2192 lungs \u2192 pulmonary veins \u2192 right ventricle\u003C/strong\u003E - The left atrium receives oxygenated blood from the pulmonary circulation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERight ventricle \u2192 pulmonary veins \u2192 lungs \u2192 pulmonary arteries \u2192 left atrium\u003C/strong\u003E - Pulmonary arteries carry blood to the lungs while pulmonary veins carry blood away from the lungs\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The pulmonary circulation carries deoxygenated blood from the right ventricle to the lungs via the pulmonary arteries.","Pulmonary arteries branch into smaller arterioles and then into capillaries surrounding alveoli where gas exchange occurs.","Oxygenated blood returns to the left atrium via pulmonary veins after gas exchange in the pulmonary capillaries."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022.","Moore KL, Dalley AF, Agur A. Clinically Oriented Anatomy. 8th ed. Lippincott Williams and Wilkins; 2017."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64795"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18470"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64795","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64795"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-14T19:54:26+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-14T19:55:06+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11199"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79473"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable 